A.3 Energy Balance & Duty Cycle
A sustainable duty cycle must account for RPS continuous output, battery cycling, and solar supplementation.

· Continuous RPS Supply: 10 kWe * 24 hr = 240 kWh/day.
· Typical Daily Demand (Excavate+Print+Ascent): ~175 kWh.
· Surplus: ~65 kWh/day used to recharge batteries from ascent load or diverted to a base grid.
· Dust Storm Mode: With solar offline, operations must be reduced. The system can maintain ~120 kWh/day for critical habitat pressurization or life support backup by scaling back excavation.

