Appendix D: Preliminary Fault Tree Analysis (FTA)

D.1 Top Undesired Event: Loss of Habitat Pressurization During Robotic Build-Out

```
TOP EVENT: Habitat Cavern Depressurization
|
├── OR Gate
│   ├── Structural Failure of Newly Excavated/Lined Section
│   │   |
│   │   ├── AND Gate
│   │   │   ├── Inadequate Structural Lining Applied
│   │   │   │   ├── Lining Material Strength Deficiency (B.1)
│   │   │   │   └── Lining Application Geometry Error (C.1)
│   │   │   └── Over-Pressurization Event
│   │   │       ├── Pressure Regulator Fault (Single Point)
│   │   │       └── Software Command Error
│   │   └── Un-Modeled Geological Fault Collapse
│   │       ├── Inadequate Pre-Excavation Subsurface Survey
│   │       └── Seismic Event
│   └── Failure of Airlock/Interface Seal
│       |
│       └── AND Gate
│           ├── Physical Damage to Seal during robotic transit
│           └── Incomplete Seal Closure Command
```

· Mitigations:
  · Lining Quality: Real-time ultrasonic testing of liner thickness and strength during application. Mandatory "cure and verify" cycle before pressurization.
  · Over-Pressurization: Two independent, mechanically redundant pressure relief valves.
  · Geological Risk: GPR pre-scan of entire excavation volume; design for a minimum Factor of Safety of 4.0.
  · Airlock Seal: Contact sensors on seal faces; positive "seal engaged" confirmation interlock before pressurization.

D.2 Critical Single Point Failure: Loss of Swarm Coordination

· Event: Corruption of the shared global_state.combined_voxel_map.
· Effect: Agents operate on contradictory maps, leading to collisions, double-work, or structural damage.
· Probability: Low (due to data integrity checks).
· Mitigation:
  1. Versioning & Checksums: All map updates are versioned with cryptographic hashes.
  2. Distributed Consensus: A Byzantine Fault Tolerant (BFT) consensus algorithm requires 2/3 of agents to agree on map state changes.
  3. Safe Default: On inability to reach consensus, all agents halt and enter a "safe-hold" pattern, awaiting ground operator intervention.

